The paper deals with scene text recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed method uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and Connectionist Temporal Classification (CTC) algorithm, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions benchmark datasets and evaluation metrics, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR).
